<h1 class="nhsuk-heading-xl">Working in the open</h1>

<p class="nhsuk-lead-paragraph">
  This project is deliberately an example to the wider NHS: a cost-effective digital project that
  focuses on end-user needs and works transparently.
</p>

<h2 class="nhsuk-heading-l">What that means in practice</h2>
<ul class="nhsuk-list nhsuk-list--bullet">
  <li><strong>Open source.</strong> The code and the prototype are public. <a class="nhsuk-link" href="{{ site.repoUrl }}">Browse the repository</a>.</li>
  <li><strong>Open decisions.</strong> Significant technical choices are recorded as architecture decision records.</li>
  <li><strong>Public-domain intent.</strong> Intellectual property is intended for maximum adoption, not monetisation.</li>
  <li><strong>Accountability by design.</strong> The service itself surfaces who accessed a plan and when — transparency built into the product, not just the process.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="nhsuk-heading-l">Roadmap &amp; decisions</h2>
<p class="nhsuk-body">
  The <a class="nhsuk-link" href="{{ site.repoUrl }}">repository</a> holds the roadmap, the architecture
  decision records, and the open issues. Contributions and scrutiny are welcome.
</p>
